    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-01-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-01-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="5"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Dayton</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 287.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-01-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 14, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of December 26, No. 247, has been
                    received, and is approved. You will express to Mr. Drouyn de l’Huys the
                    satisfaction with which the President has received Mr. Drouyn de l’Huys’s
                    assurances that instructions would be given to the French agent at New Orleans
                    to conduct matters there with prudence and moderation, avoiding occasions for
                    unnecessary difficulty, without abandoning the protection of French subjects in
                    their just rights. You will also inform Mr. Drouyn de l’Huys that reciprocal
                    instructions, with a view to avert difficulties, have been given to the military
                    authorities of the United States now occupying that city. It is confidently
                    believed that the irritations which have prevailed there will now subside.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William</hi> L. <hi rend="smallcaps">Dayton</hi>, Esq.,
                            <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
